thread.title_full: Obama plans to pitch Democrats on trade deal - SFGate

author: sfgate.com
title: Obama plans to pitch Democrats on trade deal
text:
WASHINGTON (AP) â€” President Barack Obama plans to pitch Democratic lawmakers to support a trade deal with Pacific Rim countries during a White House meeting Wednesday night.
Obama seeks Democratic support for a deal that would reduce or eliminate thousands of tariffs on U.S. goods shipped to the participating nations, which include Australia, Japan and Vietnam.
But it's not going to be an easy sell with many congressional Democrats . A key base of support, labor unions, worries that the deal would put downward pressure on wages. All of the Democrats running for president are opposing the deal.
The meeting Wednesday is with those lawmakers who helped pass legislation earlier this year that allows Obama to present Congress with proposed trade agreements that it can ratify or reject but not change.
